# Run-Analyze-Optimize

Use this rule when the user asks Cursor to run a command or workflow and iterate
until verified success or a clear blocker.

Canonical skill source:

```text
skills/run-analyze-optimize/SKILL.md
```

## Core Loop

```text
Initialize boundary
  -> Run command
  -> Observe logs/tests/artifacts
  -> Diagnose root cause
  -> Plan minimal change
  -> Worker pass
  -> Verify
  -> Independent review
  -> Decide: success / continue / blocked / budget exhausted
```

## Guardrails

- Think before coding: state assumptions and ambiguity.
- Simplicity first: use the minimum code that solves the observed problem.
- Surgical changes: every changed line must trace to the target.
- Goal-driven execution: define the verification command or artifact property.
- Roundtable-lite review: reviewer reads source and evidence directly.

## Stop Conditions

- Target verified and review passes.
- Budget exhausted.
- Two consecutive iterations have no evidence delta.
- Only sacred or unresolvable blockers remain.

Do not import full agent-roundtable infrastructure unless the user explicitly
asks for it.
